  <section class="about-card soft-card">
    <div class="about-card-title">
      <h2>a softer note</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="about-card-inner">
      <p>
        I have a lot of health stuff going on, both physical and mental, and
        sometimes that makes it very easy for me to be unkind to myself. I can
        be pretty down on how I look, how much energy I have, or how much my
        body and brain can handle.
      </p>

      <p>
        I’m trying to remember that I deserve compassion, patience, and softness
        from myself too. I’m not a project to fix. I’m a person doing her best.
      </p>

      <p class="ribbit-note">
        The demons will not win. Yes, you can tell I’m obsessed with
        <em>KPop Demon Hunters</em>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="about-card health-card">
    <div class="about-card-title">
      <h2>health stuff</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="about-card-inner">
      <p>
        These are some diagnoses that feel important to mention because they
        shape how I move through the world. They are not my whole personality,
        but they are part of my life, and having them recognised matters for my
        wellbeing.
      </p>

      <div class="diagnosis-grid">

        <div class="diagnosis-box">
          <h3>mental health / neurodivergence</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Autism, diagnosed at 17</li>
            <li>ADHD, diagnosed at 18</li>
            <li>OCD, diagnosed at 15</li>
            <li>Anxiety and depression, hanging around since I was about 12</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="diagnosis-box">
          <h3>physical health</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Ehlers-Danlos Syndrome, diagnosed at 11</li>
            <li>Raynaud’s, diagnosed at 11</li>
            <li>POTS, diagnosed at 23</li>
            <li>Silent heart murmur, diagnosed at 15</li>
            <li>Chronic pain and chronic fatigue, basically forever companions</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

      </div>

      <p>
        I’m not sharing this to brag, trauma dump, or collect pity points. It is
        simply a record of what I know about myself so far. These labels can be
        useful, especially when it comes to care, access, and understanding, but
        they are still only labels.
      </p>

      <p class="ribbit-note">
        Please get to know me for me: frog enjoyer, collector, shrine maker,
        game lover, and emotional little creature on the web.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

